Grammar Zoo

The objective of the Grammar Zoo is to accumulate grammars in a broad sense of various software languages, extracted and recovered from language documentation, parser specifications and other artefacts and make them available in a range of formats.

1029 entries and counting

1756 grammars: 1029 fetched + 639 extracted + 79 connected + 7 corrected + 1 recovered + 1 imported

Ada — API — Assembly — ATL — Automata — AWK — Basic — C — Clafer — Clojure — COBOL — C++ — C♯ — CSS — Dart — Doc — DSL — Eiffel — Erlang — Fortran — Gosu — Hardware — Haskell — HTML — Java — JavaScript — Logo — Lua — Markup — Meta — ML — Modula — Objective-C — Occam — OCL — Ontoware — Pascal — PHP — PL/I — Prolog — Python — Query — Smalltalk — Strings — Swift — Toy — Transformations — UML — XMLware — WIP
